Here is a **sample Test Plan Document** for a software testing project. You can copy this into a Word document or request a downloadable version in `.docx` or `.pdf` format.

---

# ✅ **Test Plan Document**

**Project Name:** Customer Management System
**Prepared By:** \[Your Name]
**Date:** 24-July-2025
**Version:** 1.0


-----------------
## 1. **Introduction**
---------------------------------

The purpose of this Test Plan is to define the testing strategy, scope, objectives, approach, resources, and schedule of testing activities for the **Customer Management System**. This document will serve as a guide for the QA team and stakeholders.


--------------
## 2. **Objective**
------------------------------
To ensure that the application meets the defined functional and non-functional requirements and is free from defects before release.



---------------
## 3. **Scope of Testing**
-----------------------------------------
### ✅ In Scope:

* Login and Registration Functionality
* Customer CRUD Operations
* Dashboard Data Display
* Profile Updates
* Functional and UI Testing
* Smoke and Regression Testing

### ❌ Out of Scope:

* Performance Testing
* Penetration Testing
* Third-party API response validation


-----------------
## 4. **Test Items**
----------------------
* Web Application Modules

  * Login
  * Registration
  * Customer Management
  * User Profile
  * Dashboard Metrics


-----------
## 5. **Features to Be Tested**
----------------------------------

| Feature          | Description                                  |
| ---------------- | -------------------------------------------- |
| Login Module     | Valid and invalid login checks               |
| Customer CRUD    | Add, edit, delete, and view customer details |
| Profile Settings | Update personal details                      |
| Dashboard        | Metrics display and navigation               |
| Logout           | Session timeout and logout functionality     |


-------------
## 6. **Features Not to Be Tested**
-----------------------------
* Backend database performance
* API load/stress handling
* Admin module (tested separately)


----------
## 7. **Test Strategy**
---------------------

* **Manual Testing:** For functional and UI validation
* **Automation Testing:** Selenium + Java + TestNG for regression
* **Framework:** Cucumber BDD
* **Tools:** Eclipse, Maven, Jenkins, JIRA

------------
## 8. **Test Deliverables**
--------------------------

* Test Plan Document
* Test Cases (Excel or Test Management Tool)
* Test Execution Report
* Defect Report
* Final Test Summary Report
* RTM (Requirement Traceability Matrix)

---

## 9. **Test Environment**

| Component | Details                                                      |
| --------- | ------------------------------------------------------------ |
| OS        | Windows 10, Ubuntu                                           |
| Browsers  | Chrome, Firefox                                              |
| Tools     | Selenium, TestNG, Jenkins, Postman                           |
| URL       | [http://qa.customerportal.com](http://qa.customerportal.com) |

---

## 10. **Roles & Responsibilities**

| Role        | Name          | Responsibility                     |
| ----------- | ------------- | ---------------------------------- |
| QA Lead     | Alice Johnson | Approve test plan, oversee testing |
| QA Engineer | Bob Smith     | Write and execute test cases       |
| Developer   | Charlie Lee   | Fix bugs, assist in debugging      |


----------------
## 11. **Schedule**
----------------------

| Activity           | Start Date  | End Date    |
| ------------------ | ----------- | ----------- |
| Requirement Review | 24-Jul-2025 | 25-Jul-2025 |
| Test Case Design   | 26-Jul-2025 | 28-Jul-2025 |
| Test Execution     | 29-Jul-2025 | 03-Aug-2025 |
| Defect Retesting   | 04-Aug-2025 | 06-Aug-2025 |
| Test Closure       | 07-Aug-2025 | 08-Aug-2025 |


---------
## 12. **Entry and Exit Criteria**
-----------------------------------------------
### Entry Criteria:

* Requirements are finalized and signed off
* Build is deployed in QA environment
* Test cases are reviewed and approved

### Exit Criteria:

* All planned test cases executed
* All critical/high severity defects resolved
* Test Summary Report submitted


----------
## 13. **Risks and Mitigation**
-------------------------------------------


| Risk                     | Impact | Mitigation              |
| ------------------------ | ------ | ----------------------- |
| Unclear Requirements     | High   | Frequent review with BA |
| Build delays             | Medium | Buffer time in schedule |
| Test data unavailability | Medium | Prepare mock data       |


----------
## 14. **Approvals**
---------------------------------------

| Name          | Role            | Approval |
| ------------- | --------------- | -------- |
| Alice Johnson | QA Lead         | ✅        |
| John Davis    | Project Manager | ✅        |

